The paper proposes a new recurrent neural network architecture for natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also emphasizes the importance of scalability and parallelization, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper compares the proposed architecture with convolutional models, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new initialization method for deep models, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
